The South African National Roads Agency SOC Ltd (SANRAL) would like to notify travellers that controlled blasting is scheduled to take place on Thursday, 22 June at 3pm, between Birah River and Openshaw Village along the R72.The road will be closed between Peddie turn off and Keiskamma Bridge for approximately one hour. Motorists are asked to plan their trips accordingly and to use caution when making use of the road, said Mbulelo Peterson, SANRAL Southern Region s Manager.SANRAL apologises for any inconvenience caused.